<TITLE> SC stays Osman Gani's bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court Tuesday stayed for one month the four-month bail former chief conservator of forest Osman Gani had secured from the High Court in a corruption case. The chamber judge of the Appellate Division, Md. Abdul Matin, passed the orders after the government petitioned for a freeze. Additional attorney general M Enayetur Rahim questioned the jurisdiction of the High Court to grant Gani bail in corruption cases. Moudud Ahmed, counsel for Gani, argued that with the end to emergency rule, the High Court did have the authority to grant bail in corruption cases. Gani secured bail from the High Court on Feb. 15. A special court on June 5 last year sentenced Gani to 13 years in prison for amassing wealth illegally and concealing information in his wealth statement to the Anti-Corruption Commission. The court also fined him Tk 10 lakh and ordered the authorities to confiscate his wealth worth Tk 1.80 crore, and worth Tk 2.80 crore and 270 tolas of gold ornaments of his wife. ACC deputy director Golam Shahriar Chowdhury filed the case with Uttara Police Station on July 26, 2007. In the case, Osman and his wife were accused of concealing wealth worth around Tk 4.30 crore. Joint forces arrested Osman at his Uttara house in the capital on May 29, 2007 and seized Tk 1 crore in cash that he had stashed in the house
